<div class="container policies" id="styleguidelines">
    <div class="pull-right"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>
    <div class="left-title-bar">
        <h2>Style guidelines</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="container">

        <div class="left-heading"><b>General</b> </div>
        <div>
            <p>***It is preferred that the style and tone of standard scientific writing is used, for example third-person and passive voice.
        </div>  
        <hr>

        <div class="left-heading"><b>Technical language and abbreviations</b> </div>
        <div>
            <p>Abbreviations and symbols must be standard.</p>
            <p>Acronyms must be written in full when first used. Authors should then use the same acronym for the rest of the manuscript. Acronyms should be used sparingly and only if the full phrase would be used more than 3 times in the manuscript.</p>
            <p>Drugs should be be described using their generic name whenever possible.</p>
        </div>  
        <hr>
        
        <div class="left-heading"><b>References and in-text citations</b></div>
        <div>
            <p>The APA referencing style should be used for all citations.</p>
            <p>An explanation of the APA style can be found <a href="http://www.apastyle.org/">here</a>http://www.apastyle.org/.</p>
            <p>Unofficial references should be avoided but, if deemed necessary, they should be cited in parentheses.</p>
        </div>      

   </div>
</div>
